Business Brief -- U.S. Shoe Corp.:
   Sales in Latest Five Weeks
   Rose 4.2% to $175 Million
In the women's apparel division, January sales were $89.3
million, down 1.6% from the year-ago period. Same-store sales
for the month rose 4%. For the year, sales were $1.36
billion, up 2.1% from a year earlier. Same-store sales for
the year, not counting divested stores, rose 2.1%. The group
had 1,585 stores at the end of January, compared with 1,763 a
year earlier.